<a name="intro"></a>
This is the very first Stupid <a href="#pixarTM">RenderMan®</a> Tricks (SRT).  Unfortunately, I don't have much here.<p>
Here is what I have so far:<p>
<pre>
Speakers:
David Block -- Visual Shaders
Katsuaki HIRAMITSU -- clouds and sea surface shaders
Ivan DeWolf -- nonlinear displacements
Tom Duff -- talked about PRMan's RiBlobby primitive
</pre>
So far only David Block has written me and gave me a link to his talk.
    <hr>
<a name="visshading"></a>
<H2>Visualization Shading</H2>
Here are the <a href="http://woodall.ncsa.uiuc.edu/dbock/Presentations/RmanUsersGroup.ppt">PowerPoint slides</a> from  <a href="http://woodall.ncsa.uiuc.edu/dbock/">David Block's</a> talk on the topic of shaders for use in scientific visualization.
<P>
More information on his work in this area can be found at:
<a href="http://woodall.ncsa.uiuc.edu/dbock/projects/VisShade/">VisShade</a>
<p>
